open_q0: It quickly became clear that sometimes the "holes" in the forcefield could either be black OR white, so it became a sort of guessing game at some point. With forcefields that were similar and one clearly had more black, that was the one that I assessed to be weaker, and there seemed to be a pattern.
open_q1: It was clear once shooting all the spaceship types which ones gave the best reward
open_q2: This is where it got more complex. The same rules applied to the forcefield, where the weakness could either be represented by black or white, so it was a toss up between the forcefield choice. A big deciding factor was the spaceship type when choosing to shoot at one or the other. Sometimes, even if the forcefield seemed weaker on the spaceship that gave a lower reward, it was worth the gamble to shoot at the spaceship with the higher reward given the uncertainty of the forcefield color. In situations where the spaceships were the same, the choice was made using only the forcefield. In some cases where there was a low reward ship next to a high reward ship, if the low reward ship had a forcefield that I perceived as being the definite weaker one, I would shoot at the lower reward ship to get the points rather than most likely getting no points if I shot at the higher reward ship that was more likely to have the stronger forcefield.
